So I ordered an old fashion and a burger at the bar. My friend ordered shrimp and grits. I took a sip of my drink and it tasted like straight salt. I asked "is this an old fashioned" bartender said "yes" I took another look noticed a fly in it and sent the drink back. Second drink arrives and it still taste like a salt lick! I asked the bartender if she was putting salt in my drink she said "no its sugar" I told her she need to check again even offered her a taste. She did check and realized that she had in fact been putting salt in my drink. She makes me  another drink in the same glass that had now had two rounds of salt and a fly in it. So naturally my drink was still salty...🤨 she didn't comp my drink and acted like it was someone else fault...🤨 I know salt and sugar look similar but any bartender worth their "salt," pun intended, preps there bar before starting and knows what's what. Most bartenders also take a straw full of a drink to taste it to make sure it's right. None of this happend hense my 3 glasses of sea water. Further more the food was bland and tasteless so I suppose that is why the salty drink. My advice steer clear!

Let's talk about SKYTOWN.  This is one of the best places I've ever been to, my adoration of it knows no bounds.  SKYTOWN is open late. It has a stylish interior, even for an upscale bar. It's not too noisy.  The wait staff are great. They were very nice to me every time I have been there.  The food is phenomenal. They have some seriously good, inventive options. The steak sandwich is delicious. The fried chicken and waffles, while nontraditional (a bit of a smaller waffle tan typical, already split, presented beautifully, with boneless chicken that is lightly fried and seasoned very well), is some of the best I have ever had. The brunch deal here is great, and given there is no outdoor seating it is a secret brunch spot. It was almost empty on a Saturday at noon.  If you live in the area and you aren't a regular here, you're missing out.

caption: One of the things with dining out in nyc is the inconsistency of the fare: depending on who’s in the back of the house, the food could be amazing, mediocre, or worse. This has never been the case at Skytown, it is consistent and it is consistently GOOD. After we hadn’t been in a while, my wife and I stopped in to grab a bite and a booze. We forgot just how amazing the tacos are, and sampled the beef stew which was equally amazing. Although they are Americanized, not traditional style tacos, they are definitely my favorite meal in New York. The service is also amazingly consistent, never bad and certainly never mediocre.

Grease total nightmare. I order a burger and a beer yesterday, waitress asked "how would you like your burger" my answer, medium. Burger came and if you been there know the place is dark to really see what is in your plate, I ate it not knowing that I was eating an almost raw f...g Turkey burger and I ate it fast, I didn't really want to stay long with all the grease smelly smoke from the kitchen, it would stick to you and not leave until you shower.The real nightmare started at 2 am when the burger made its way out through almost all holes in my body. Whomever owns this place, change your menu, inform your cooks Turkey burgers can't be medium done because of salmonella, don't sell food or close but, try not to kill anyone with your food and be thankful I am writing this review so people can be informed and I am not calling health department on you.
